@page
@using MP.GameEngine.Helpers.RuleSet
@inject IConfiguration Config
@model UltimateMonopoly.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    ViewData["Description"] = $"How {RuleDictionary.GameName} handles your data — what we collect, how it is used, and your rights.";

    var webUrl = Config["Routes:WebUrl"] ?? "https://www.monappoly.com/";
    ViewData["Canonical"] = $"{webUrl}Privacy";

    var email = Config["Communication:Email:ContactRecipient"] ?? "support@monappoly.com";
    var publisherUrl = Config["Routes:PublisherUrl"] ?? "https://www.jcfoundry.co.uk";
}

<article class="py-4 mx-auto" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h1 class="h3 mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-4">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <div class="alert alert-secondary small" role="note">
        @RuleDictionary.GameName is an independent, unofficial fan project. It is <strong>not</strong> affiliated
        with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Hasbro, Inc. MONOPOLY&reg; is a trademark of Hasbro. The app is free to use.
    </div>

    <p>
        This policy explains what personal data @RuleDictionary.GameName ("we", "us") collects when you use the app,
        why we collect it, and the choices you have. The app is operated by
        <a href="@publisherUrl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JC Foundry</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">1. Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong> — the email address, username, and display name you provide when
            you register, plus your (hashed) password. Email is used to confirm your account or recovery.</li>
        <li><strong>Gameplay data</strong> — the games you create or join, your moves, statistics, board skins, and
            related history, so the app can run games and show your stats.</li>
        <li><strong>Social data</strong> — friend connections, friend requests, blocks, and direct messages you send
            to friends through the app.</li>
        <li><strong>Support &amp; feedback</strong> — the contents of any contact message, feedback, or bug report
            you submit. Email content is <strong>not</strong> stored on our system(s).</li>
        <li><strong>Technical data</strong> — a session/authentication cookie to keep you signed in, and basic
            server logs (e.g. errors and admin actions) needed to operate and secure the service.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="small text-body-secondary">
        We do <strong>not</strong> take any payment information — the app is free — and we do not run third-party
        advertising or sell your data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. How we use your data</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>To create and run your account and your games.</li>
        <li>To provide the social features (friends, messaging) and your statistics.</li>
        <li>To keep the service secure — spam/abuse prevention, moderation, and audit logging of actions.</li>
        <li>To reply to your support messages and fix reported issues.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        We use only essential cookies required to sign you in and keep your session secure. We do not use tracking
        or advertising cookies.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Email</h2>
    <p>
        We send email only for account purposes — confirming your address, account recovery, and replying to
        contact or issue messages. We do not send marketing email.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Sharing &amp; third parties</h2>
    <p>
        We do not sell or rent your personal data. Data is shared only with the service providers we rely on to run
        the app (such as our hosting provider and the email delivery service used to send account emails), and where
        required by law. Some information is visible to other players by design — for example your display name and/or username, and
        public statistics on the leaderboard, unless you hide your profile.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">6. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
        We keep your account data while your account is active. Completed and abandoned games may be cleaned up
        automatically after a period of time. If you delete your account, your personal account data is removed;
        some anonymised or aggregate records may remain where needed for the integrity of past games.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">7. Your rights &amp; choices</h2>
    <p>
        You can view and update your details, download a copy of your personal data, and permanently delete your
        account from your
        @if (User.Identity?.IsAuthenticated == true)
        {
            <a asp-area="Identity" asp-page="/Account/Manage/Index">account settings</a>
        }
        else
        {
            <text>account settings</text>
        }
        (Account &rsaquo; Personal Data). You can also hide your profile from the public leaderboard at any time.
        For any other request, contact us using the details below.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">8. Children</h2>
    <p>
        The app is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal data from them. If
        you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will remove it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by the "last updated" date
        above.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        Questions about this policy or your data? Email us at
        <a href="mailto:@email">@email</a>.
    </p>
</article>